init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Notes about this, notes about that, notes with interesting facts on them about the number of people who died by lawnmower in 2004.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A few hours later, you're in a plane with a bunch of other former Presidents.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There's a lady from the Truman administration, who doesn't seem to have aged at all.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There's a man from Lincoln's administration, who resembles a giant bear.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: there's a man from Eisenhower's administration, who seems to be missing an arm.
